snippet: Andy Murray's brilliant returning was always going to be a handful for Milos Raonic but it was the quality of the Briton's serve that proved decisive in the world number two's advance to a fifth Australian Open final on Friday....
lead_paragraph: Andy Murray's brilliant returning was always going to be a handful for Milos Raonic but it was the quality of the Briton's serve that proved decisive in the world number two's advance to a fifth Australian Open final on Friday.

headline.print_headline: Returning Maestro Murray Shows Quality of His Serve
headline.main: Returning Maestro Murray Shows Quality of His Serve
